Date: 5 Dec 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: CNN 5 Dec 2001 6:16 PM EST (2316 GMT) [edited
<http://www.cnn.com/2001/HEALTH/conditions/12/05/anthrax.leahy.letter/index.

html>


Scientists begin to open Leahy anthrax letter
---------------------------------------------
Scientists at Fort Detrick, a germ warfare research lab in Maryland, began
on Wednesday the process of opening an anthrax-contaminated letter
addressed to Sen. Patrick Leahy, according to the FBI. The letter was
discovered and quarantined 16 Nov 2001.

Scientists hope to carefully extract the anthrax from the letter and
preserve much of it to analyze and learn its source. They may open the
letter further another day to actually take the letter out.

--
[And now some good news. - Mod.MHJ

